1
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:20,867
I'm okay.

2
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:30,667
Can you please not smile
like that?

3
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:35,100
- Sorry, why?
- Just don't.

4
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,933
Wait, my car and my stuff,
won't it get stolen?

5
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,200
It's safe. The people here
are kind.

6
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,700
What's with you,
as if you don't know.

7
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:46,200
I don't know. I haven't been
back here for a long time.

8
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,633
How easy for you to forget.

9
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:49,000
So what's next?

10
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:50,233
I will stay here?

11
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,833
I can't stay here.

12
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:53,767
I'll die.

13
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:57,433
I'm sorry, Ma'am,
but we have to prove

14
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:58,567
that you did not do that
intentionally

15
00:00:58,633 --> 00:01:00,533
or you did not intend
to destroy the property.

16
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,133
And what happened is an act
of negligence.

17
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,533
Just relax. Don't panic.

18
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:05,600
I'll go there.

19
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:07,533
I'll call my cousin Winston.

20
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:09,267
He's the best lawyer in town.

21
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:11,567
I already asked to prepare
the chopper.

22
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,000
Just text me where you are,
I'll meet you there.

23
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:16,667
You don't understand.

24
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:21,700
I can't stay long here because
I'm not from here anymore.

25
00:01:21,767 --> 00:01:22,967
You are still from here.

26
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:24,733
You were born here.
You grew up here.

27
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,000
But this is where I got hurt

28
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:27,833
and here is where the people
who have hurt me.

29
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,733
But wherever I am now...

30
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:32,700
I worked hard for it.

31
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,233
I worked hard for it.

32
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:43,033
So don't tell me that
I'm selfish and judge me

33
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,400
because I'm not like that.

34
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:47,033
This conversation
is going nowhere.

35
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,633
If you don't want to come
with me to Sorsogon...

36
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,000
I will not force you.

37
00:01:53,567 --> 00:01:55,733
What happened to my cuz
is driving me crazy.

38
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,567
Yes, I've been looking
for Celeste here in town.

39
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:00,533
I've been driving around
already. I hope I can find her.

40
00:02:05,067 --> 00:02:06,067
No more tears, Love.

41
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:08,233
I'm here.

42
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:11,133
Everything will be
taken cared of.

43
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:13,500
Did you find her?

44
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,033
- Yes.
- Good thing you're here.

45
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,933
Is she with you?

46
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,633
Can I talk to her?

47
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,200
She's not with me.

48
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,400
She's okay.

49
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:23,500
Don't worry anymore.

50
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:28,733
I consider what you did
as a negligent act.

51
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,700
Reckless imprudence
resulting in damage to property.

52
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:34,167
Attorney, what I really want
to know is...

53
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:35,933
am I going to jail?

54
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,733
Well instead of going to jail...

55
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,900
we should apply for probation,
Celeste.

56
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,967
You are required to do
community service.

57
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:45,467
Which is a minimum of one month
and one day

58
00:02:45,533 --> 00:02:48,833
to a maximum of six months
full for major arrest.

59
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:49,500
What?

60
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,433
Delicious?

61
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,267
Delicious?

62
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:53,567
This is the most delicious
 pinangat that I've ever tasted

63
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:54,733
in my whole life.

64
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,700
You just love me, Grandma.

65
00:04:57,767 --> 00:04:58,833
Yes, of course.

66
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,467
You are my only grandchild.

67
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,067
I love you so much

68
00:05:02,167 --> 00:05:05,400
that's why
I named you after me.

69
00:05:05,467 --> 00:05:09,967
Ikay, Mikoy, Ikay,
Mikoy, sounds like.

70
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:14,100
That's why my name sounds awful.

71
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:16,200
Don't laugh at our names.

72
00:05:16,267 --> 00:05:19,933
What's with you?

73
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,833
Do you remember when you
and Celeste were young?

74
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,933
We often cook this.

75
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,867
Be careful.

76
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:35,967
There you go.

77
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:46,833
The secret of a delicious
pinangat is in coconut milk.

78
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,567
Your turn, try it.

79
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:49,600
How?

80
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:53,267
First, okay let me show you.

81
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:55,933
There...

82
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,467
you squeeze it here.

83
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:59,867
Then you put it there.

84
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:00,900
Go ahead.

85
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,400
Get some.

86
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:05,467
You can do it.

87
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,867
That's it, see?

88
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:13,233
- There you go.
- Is it right?

89
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:14,900
Go ahead.

90
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:16,000
There you go.

91
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:23,933
You're good.

92
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,133
- Really?
- You learned fast.

93
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,900
- Go ahead.
- It's done.

94
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:35,867
That's right.

95
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:37,633
You learned fast.

96
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:40,167
Now you know how to
squeeze coconut milk.

97
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,533
That's the most important
of all.

98
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:46,667
It will give life to pinangat.

99
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:49,500
Then you cut
the ingredients.

100
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:56,300
You use the red one and
include the green one.

101
00:06:56,367 --> 00:07:01,000
Pinangat can't be without chili.

102
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,500
Do you understand?

103
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:05,867
- Yes.
- Okay, there you go.

104
00:07:05,933 --> 00:07:07,900
You should do your best
when it's your turn.

105
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,567
Why does it seem
so easy for her?

106
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,033
You just don't know.

107
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,833
Grandma...

108
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:24,067
you remember Celeste
in everything we cooked.

109
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:25,600
Yes, of course.

110
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:28,867
Somehow my memory
is still sharp.

111
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:32,000
Until now I know how much
you love Celeste.

112
00:07:32,067 --> 00:07:33,767
That was before...

113
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:34,933
but not anymore.

114
00:07:36,467 --> 00:07:38,900
By the way, she's here.

115
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:41,600
Really, you saw each other?

116
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:45,700
Why didn't you tell her
to come and visit me?

117
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:49,200
I wasn't able to tell her that.

118
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,900
Is she still mad at you?

119
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:54,733
It seems not anymore.

120
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:59,000
We both have moved on, Grandma.

121
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,167
I hope it's the same for all.

122
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,600
- Delicious?
- It's delicious.

123
00:08:07,033 --> 00:08:08,200
Is it spicy?

124
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,867
You should eat more.

125
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:11,433
- Go ahead.
- How about you?

126
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,233
Why don't you join me?

127
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:14,467
One big mouthful, Grandma.

128
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,400
I might finish it all.

129
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:23,100
Take care of the orders.

130
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,767
Be careful driving.

131
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,500
All the pinangat that
we worked hard on last night

132
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:29,500
might just go to waste.

133
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:31,533
Yes, Grandma.

134
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,433
I'll take care of it.

135
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:38,633
By the way, bring the three
trays to Patricio and Adora.

136
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,633
To Celeste?

137
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:41,933
Yes, Grandson.

138
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:45,200
Patricio ordered
for that last week.

139
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:48,500
Okay.

140
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:49,733
Close it.

141
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,267
Just be careful.

142
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:54,333
Yes.

143
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:01,467
Love...

144
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:03,333
thank you so much
for saving me

145
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,533
from this horrible situation.

146
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,000
Love...

147
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:11,267
you matter to me.

148
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:12,467
This too will be fixed.

149
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:16,567
I hope so.

150
00:09:16,633 --> 00:09:19,200
I can't wait to go home
with you.

151
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,600
Love...

152
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,833
before we go back
to Manila,

153
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:25,500
can we drop by
your family's place?

154
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:27,367
I want to meet your family.

155
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:33,767
Okay.

156
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:45,900
Bro, just eat.

157
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:48,367
Just get what you want
on the table.

158
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:49,533
- Yes. Yes.
- Okay?

159
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,233
- Go back, May-May.
- Thank you.

160
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,233
Don't be shy.

161
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,233
Good morning, Ms. Adora,
Mr. Patricio.

162
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,800
- Mikoy.
- Here's the pinangat

163
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:57,200
that you ordered.

164
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,467
Thank you.

165
00:09:58,533 --> 00:10:01,467
You know, I've been craving
for Grandma Ikay's specialty

166
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:03,067
since yesterday.

167
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:05,667
Mikoy, one day I'll visit you.

168
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,833
Okay.

169
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,600
Mikoy.

170
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:12,233
Did you tell them about Celeste?

171
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:13,300
No.

172
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:15,133
I don't want them to worry.

173
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,833
- That's right.
- Let's eat.

174
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,533
No, thanks.

175
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,667
I'll go ahead.

176
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:23,033
Mikoy, are you leaving?

177
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,033
Yes.

178
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,367
Don't go yet.

179
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:27,067
You should eat first.

180
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:30,033
No, thank you.
It's embarrassing.

181
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,400
What do you mean
it's embarrassing?

182
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:33,167
Mikoy, you are like our son.

183
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,167
Here.

184
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,933
I'm still going to Matnog.

185
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,533
I'll buy lobster there.

186
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,567
Mikoy, I will feel bad

187
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,200
if you will not grant
my request.

188
00:10:41,267 --> 00:10:42,367
You should eat first.

189
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:44,600
Come on.

190
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:46,600
You eat first before
you go to Matnog.

191
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:50,033
What is this, Mikoy? Is there
a cab waiting outside?

192
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,000
Why are you in a hurry?

193
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:53,600
- You should eat first.
 - You shut up.

194
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:55,567
Uncle Patricio prepared
delicious food.

195
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:57,767
Okay, thank you.

196
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,533
- Just get food there.
- Just go there.

197
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,200
So...

198
00:11:09,267 --> 00:11:15,400
this is it. We're here.

199
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:17,000
I'm so excited that

200
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:21,167
I will finally be able
to meet your family.

201
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:22,133
- Father.
- Yes?

202
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,267
It's Celeste.

203
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,733
Huh, it's Celeste?

204
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,800
Hey...

205
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,167
she's here.

206
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,500
Celeste?

207
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:55,600
I'm Tonito, Sir.

208
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:58,333
I'm Celeste's fiancé.

209
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,900
Yeah, I heard.

210
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:04,100
We were just surprised by
my daughter's sudden decision.

211
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:07,433
But she's at the right age.

212
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:13,000
You should've told us
that you will bring Tonito here.

213
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:16,300
I was the one who actually
insisted, Sir.

214
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,633
We're in a hurry because
Tonito is also busy.

215
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:21,633
So we will not stay long.

216
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,633
Actually, I want to invite you
for dinner, Sir.

217
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,133
If that's okay with you?

218
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,967
You know we also prepared
a small gathering.

219
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:30,600
Maybe it would be better
if we eat here.

220
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:35,567
So you will taste the food
Celeste grew up with.

221
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,200
Wow, I'm so excited, Sir.

222
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:42,767
I heard that food here
in Sorsogon is delicious.

223
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:44,400
Not just delicious,

224
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:48,800
It's more tasty if we eat
together with our family.

225
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:49,767
Just in time.

226
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,800
Your cousin May-May
is here and...

227
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:55,000
- where are they?
- They went ahead.

228
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:58,167
Mikoy really needs to go
to Matnog.

229
00:12:58,233 --> 00:13:00,200
Is that so?
They left already.

230
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:02,333
That's great, that's okay.

231
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:06,867
At least it's just us,
I mean, family.

232
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:08,600
Is that so? Come on.

233
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:11,067
You come in. Come on.

234
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,633
This way.

235
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:28,333
What's with you, Mikoy?

236
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,833
Why did we leave right away?

237
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:35,100
What's this? I just ate
a few shrimp and mussels.

238
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:38,367
It didn't even reach
my esophagus.

239
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:39,567
There is a lot of food
in the house.

240
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:41,633
If you want, you can eat first.

241
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,433
That's not only what I want.

242
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,267
I also want to meet
Celeste's husband-to-be.

243
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:48,033
Aren't you curious?

244
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,833
That's why I left

245
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:54,567
because I don't want
the situation to be awkward.

246
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,267
Why would it be awkward?

247
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:04,533
Are you insensitive
or you're just numb?

248
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,767
All of the above.

249
00:14:06,933 --> 00:14:09,433
You know that Celeste
is my former girlfriend, right?

250
00:14:11,933 --> 00:14:14,667
I'm sure I'm the last person
she wants to be there

251
00:14:14,733 --> 00:14:16,733
on the day she will introduce
her husband-to-be

252
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,333
to her family that's why I left.

253
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:23,033
Wow, you're the sensitive one,
Mikoy.

254
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:23,800
Okay, okay.

255
00:14:23,867 --> 00:14:26,367
It's you who gave way.

256
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:29,833
Enough with your remarks.

257
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:34,200
Okay, you might cry there.

258
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:38,333
But in fairness with cuz Celeste

259
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:41,700
she has a different way
of getting a man.

260
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:45,267
Just one look at her
future husband

261
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:48,400
and you know he's a big shot.

262
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:53,833
He looks very successful
and accomplished.

263
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:56,900
He also looks kind and caring.

264
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:59,267
And most of all...

265
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:02,333
he looks yummy.

266
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:09,900
I'm happy for her because cuz
deserves that kind of man.

267
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:16,733
Cuz deserves to catch
a bigger fish in the sea.

268
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:22,100
Sorry, I didn't know
you're there.

269
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,167
Can I say sorry?

270
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:28,167
Yummy?

271
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,567
Go ahead and eat.

272
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,767
Ouch, okay.

273
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:48,133
This is good.

274
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:51,333
We call that pinangat.

275
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:54,933
That's one of the famous
dishes here

276
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:58,033
and that's Grandma Ikay's
recipe.

277
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:01,000
You know, I'm sure
you will be happy

278
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:02,667
once you meet her grandson.

279
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:04,533
It's Mikoy.

280
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,067
Aren't you close before,
Celeste?

281
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:12,133
Well, I would like to meet
this Grandma Ikay

282
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,867
and this friend
of yours, Celeste.

283
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,900
Oh no, it's okay,
don't waste your time.

284
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:20,167
We don't talk anymore.

285
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,400
But maybe you can ask
Grandma Ikay to prepare this

286
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:25,067
for our wedding.

287
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:26,233
I'll think about it.

288
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,067
When is the wedding?

289
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:33,833
Well, nothing is set
in stone yet.

290
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:37,933
But I was hoping to get you
and Ma'am Adora involved here.

291
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,133
I hope that's okay
with you, Celeste.

292
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,100
I don't mind.

293
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,367
I don't mind.

294
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:49,500
This is something that
really bothers me.

295
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:54,833
I don't know Celeste's life here
in Sorsogon.

296
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:57,200
Because I'm about to marry
the most wonderful woman

297
00:16:57,267 --> 00:16:58,800
that I've ever met.

298
00:16:58,867 --> 00:17:02,633
And there are so many new things
that I need to know about her.

299
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:06,133
But every new thing that
I learned about her,

300
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,400
makes me love her all the more.

301
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:16,333
I'm sorry for being overly
dramatic and cheesy but

302
00:17:16,433 --> 00:17:18,067
I know that Celeste loves that.

303
00:17:22,467 --> 00:17:25,733
I know that
you're a busy person.

304
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:31,733
What I can say to you is that
this house is...

305
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:36,900
always open to the person
that my daughter loves.

306
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:46,300
We are not a perfect family.

307
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:48,033
We are not rich.

308
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,967
We might not be that
influential in life.

309
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:58,033
But what's important to us
is to see the two of you happy

310
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,233
in the decision
that you will make.

311
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:05,600
Now I'm the one who will
apologize to you

312
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:09,333
because it's me
who is being overly dramatic.

313
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:16,433
Sebastian, you should keep
your cellphone first.

314
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,900
We're still eating.

315
00:18:17,967 --> 00:18:19,000
Sorry, Mother.

316
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:21,567
My friend just texted me.

317
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:24,567
Celeste is viral.

318
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:26,233
What?

319
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:28,700
Celeste, you're a trending topic
right now.

320
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:10,967
Grandma, you startled me.

321
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:13,633
I'm just checking
if you are still breathing.

322
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:16,167
You've been sitting quietly here
for quite some time.

323
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:18,800
Is there something
bothering you?

324
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:19,800
Did someone fight with you?

325
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:22,933
Just tell me,
I'll punch him.

326
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,567
Nothing, Grandma.

327
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:26,900
Are you sure there's nothing?

328
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:28,400
There's nothing, Grandma.

329
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,233
You can lie to the whole world

330
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,867
but you can't lie
to your Grandma Ikay.

331
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:34,867
You won't get away with it.

332
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:36,533
I was the one who cut
your umbilical cord

333
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,700
so I know you very well.

334
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:40,300
Even if you don't tell me,

335
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,033
I know that you're going through
something.

336
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:50,533
See, your sigh is deeper
than a well.

337
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:58,367
Have I done something good
with my life?

338
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,900
Can you consider me...

339
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,500
successful?

340
00:20:06,567 --> 00:20:07,633
Accomplished?

341
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:11,433
Why did you ask that?

342
00:20:16,267 --> 00:20:17,267
I don't know.

343
00:20:19,167 --> 00:20:21,033
Never mind, my question
is nonsense, Grandma.

344
00:20:23,267 --> 00:20:27,833
For me, you are very successful
and accomplished.

345
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:32,233
Now if you tell me that
you're not successful

346
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:33,567
because you don't have
the money,

347
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:37,267
you have a low measure
of success.

348
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:40,167
If wealth or money
is only the gauge,

349
00:20:40,233 --> 00:20:45,733
then many thieves and corrupt

350
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:50,367
can be considered very
successful and accomplished.

351
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:55,067
For me, you are very successful
and accomplished

352
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:57,333
because you're here.

353
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:00,133
You help the people here.

354
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:06,700
You share your expertise
and your time to help

355
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,200
other people around you.

356
00:21:10,133 --> 00:21:12,400
If you think about it...

357
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,967
you can go to Manila.

358
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:18,733
You can apply to a big
corporation or company.

359
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:21,333
Many will hire you
but you didn't.

360
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:24,467
You choose to stay here
in Sorsogon.

361
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:28,400
That's why a lot of people here
respect and look up to you.

362
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:34,000
So for me,
my most handsome grandson

363
00:21:34,067 --> 00:21:37,000
is very successful
and accomplished.

364
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,233
Grandma, we're going
to sell these

365
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:39,433
and you're spreading
your saliva.

366
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,367
And besides, I'm your most
handsome grandson

367
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:45,067
because I'm your only grandson.

368
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:47,600
So you would know
that I'm not lying.

369
00:21:49,167 --> 00:21:54,133
Mikoy!

370
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,867
Hey, your ex-sweetheart
is a trending topic right now.

371
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:00,433
Who among them?

372
00:22:08,667 --> 00:22:10,700
You're not cute.

373
00:22:10,767 --> 00:22:11,733
You're ugly.

374
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:14,133
Why are you even facing me?

375
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,967
This is a horrible,
horrible view.

376
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:19,967
This is really bad.

377
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:22,767
Do you know that the facepad
of the Municipal Hall

378
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,100
is flooded with negative
comments?

379
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,300
That I'm not doing anything.

380
00:22:27,433 --> 00:22:29,600
That I'm useless.

381
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:32,633
That I just let the rich step
on the dignity

382
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,700
of the Sorsoguenos.

383
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,267
Look at my eye bags...

384
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:37,367
it's big.

385
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:38,533
I didn't get enough sleep

386
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,333
deleting the negative comments
last night.

387
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:44,667
And my day is ruined because
when I woke up this morning,

388
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:46,767
there are more bashers.

389
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:49,967
Actually, Mayor, you can turn
off the comment section

390
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:51,767
of our social media page.

391
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:52,867
Really?

392
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:55,633
But that's not good

393
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:58,300
because the people will get more
agitated if you do that.

394
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,933
Don't you have
a Social Media Manager?

395
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,233
You know that we don't have
a budget right now

396
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,900
to hire a Social Media Manager.

397
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:10,100
But we have
a big problem right now.

398
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:13,300
How can we solve this?

399
00:23:13,367 --> 00:23:15,333
For sure, I'll be blamed.

400
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:19,700
Our people will think that
I can't fight for them

401
00:23:19,767 --> 00:23:21,933
against someone
from Manila.

402
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,233
Well, technically,
Celeste is from Sorsogon.

403
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:26,400
She grew up here.

404
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:30,900
You know, Mayor, maybe
we shouldn't be impulsive

405
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,033
with our decision.

406
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:34,633
Besides, the case is already
in the fiscal

407
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:37,533
so we should let them decide.

408
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:38,633
What are you saying?

409
00:23:38,700 --> 00:23:40,067
Let's not do anything?

410
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,133
It's not that
we won't do anything.

411
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,667
Let's not be carried away
by our emotions.

412
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:45,967
Once this issue settles down,

413
00:23:46,033 --> 00:23:48,267
I'm sure we can think
of something good to do.

414
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:51,533
Maybe you're suggesting that

415
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:54,600
because Celeste
is your former love?

416
00:23:56,133 --> 00:23:57,200
Of course not.

417
00:23:57,267 --> 00:23:58,733
Why are you so defensive?

418
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:01,900
Celeste...

419
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:06,200
see how you react?

420
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:08,600
It manifests in your face
that every time Celeste's name

421
00:24:08,667 --> 00:24:12,467
is mentioned,
you are very much affected.

422
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:19,133
I think I have a brilliant idea
on how to deal with this.

423
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:45,333
I just actually
have to stay here

424
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,400
for a couple of days
or maybe weeks.

425
00:24:48,467 --> 00:24:49,533
How is your sister Vivian?

426
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:51,067
Is she still pissed off with me?

427
00:24:51,133 --> 00:24:52,733
I haven't heard anything
from her.

428
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:55,900
I guess she thinks that this
crisis is handled brilliantly.

429
00:24:55,967 --> 00:24:57,633
I hope we won't have a problem.

430
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:59,400
Why would we have a problem?

431
00:24:59,467 --> 00:25:00,433
Just do what is right.

432
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:02,800
I'll be fair with what I'll tell
the court.

433
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:06,033
We keep on having lunch and
dinner as if nothing is wrong.

434
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:09,367
Dad, just tell the truth
because this is just a façade.

435
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:12,200
Because we're not happy,
we're not complete.

436
00:25:12,267 --> 00:25:15,333
This is not real
because you gave up on us.

437
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,967
But many things
can't be changed.

438
00:25:18,033 --> 00:25:21,833
Like the memories,
we can't change that.

439
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:23,800
Do you know that
I met you here?

440
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:26,600
What happened with her
and Tonito?

441
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:29,033
They fought again
about Celeste.

442
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:31,433
This fashion designer
is all over my feed.

443
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:33,333
You know this Celeste, right?

444
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,667
Isn't she dating your dad?

445
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:39,600
You did not fight hard
for your love, for your family.

446
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:40,700
Vivian.

447
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,533
No, it's true.

448
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:45,567
I sincerely believe that you
and Tonito look good together.

449
00:25:45,633 --> 00:25:48,467
She's a no match to me, Loser.

450
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,767
- Loser?
- Yes, Loser.

451
00:25:54,467 --> 00:25:56,300
Tiff, Tiff...

452
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:59,900
Tonito...

453
00:25:59,967 --> 00:26:03,867
can we be a couple again?

454
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,800
Are you sure that's what
you'll wear on the first day

455
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,000
of your community service?

456
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:12,433
Never miss an opportunity
to make a good impression.

457
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:16,933
As the Italian say,
La Bella Figura.

458
00:26:17,867 --> 00:26:20,367
Let's leave so you can
make La Bella figura.

459
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:21,400
Let's go.
